Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State says 64 people have tested positive for COVID-19 in the state. Makinde, who stated this via his Twitter handle, said the five new confirmed cases announced by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Saturday night, brought the number to 64. He tweeted, “The COVID-19 confirmation tests for five suspected cases came back positive. READ ALSO: Poor diet may affect COVID-19 patients’ survival —Nutritionists “The cases are from the following local government areas: Ibadan North (two), a foreigner in Surulere, Ibadan North East (one) and Ibadan South West (one). “So, the total number of confirmed cases in Oyo State is 64.” He urged the general public to call the emergency operations centre, if they found travellers from other states arriving in their neighbourhood. Five new confirmed cases in the state were among the 239 recorded in 15 states on Saturday by the NCDC. (NAN)